EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 162300 UTC
THROUGH FRIDAY EVENING AND SUNDAY A COMPLEX LOW PRESSURE
SYSTEM IN THE EERN ATLANTIC AND ACROSS WERN EUROPE WILL
SWING THUNDERY LOW PRESSURE CENTRES NWARDS ACROSS THE UK.
HIGH PRESSURE WILL LIE ACROSS SCANDINAVIA. THROUGH SUNDAY
ONE LOW PRESSURE CENTRE WILL MIGRATE INTO EERN EUROPE
AND ANOTHER TO THE S OF ICELAND. A COL AREA WILL DEVELOP
ACROSS THE UK AS THE SCANDINAVIAN HIGH PRESSURE BEGINS TO
JOIN UP WITH THE AZORES HIGH. PRESSURE WILL CONTINUE TO
BUILD ACROSS THE UK ON MONDAY WITH A DEEP AREA OF LOW
PRESSURE BECMG CENTRED IN MID-ATLANTIC. THROUGH FRIDAY
EVENING AND SATURDAY SE WINDS WILL BE OCNL STRG IN THE N
SEA INCLUDING THAMES BUT REMAIN LIGHTER IN DOVER AND
WIGHT. THE STRG WINDS WILL SPREAD NWARDS THROUGH SUNDAY
BECMG CONFINED TO VIKING N AND S UTSIRE FORTIES FISHER
AND FAIR ISLE BY THE END OF THE DAY. WINDS WILL MOD IN
ALL SEA AREAS THROUGH MONDAY
